Here in northern Illinois we are in the densest concentration of nuclear reactors in the US (there are 14 in northern Ill and a bunch more in surrounding states. Three of the fourteen have been off-lined). Ralph Nader once called ComEd &quot;the nuclear mad dog of the Midwest&quot;. ComEd has the highest number of penalty fines per reactor of any utility.<br>
<br>
Exelon has wanted to get back into the nuclear business for a long time. However, light water reactors (LWR) cost 5 times the alternatives. When South Africa considered dabbling with an experimental new design the PBMR, Exelon became interested. They proposed building them in the US without containment systems and no safety exclusion zone. They figured that without these basic safety systems, then they could build them for only triple the cost of the alternatives.<br>
This was the (feeble) basis for the hope that the US would have new reactor orders.<br>
<br>
